modules.description: This module implements the ChaCha encryption and decryption algorithms, supporting ChaCha20, ChaCha12, and ChaCha8 variants. It operates on cryptographic keys (16 or 32 bytes) and 8-byte nonces to generate a state, which is then used to transform input data into encrypted or decrypted output. It is suitable for secure communication protocols and data encryption where stream ciphers are preferred.

This module implements the ChaCha stream cipher in three variants—20, 12, and 8 rounds—transforming input data into encrypted output using a defined key schedule and block function. It operates directly on `Cstruct.t` values, which represent memory buffers for cryptographic operations. It is used for high-speed encryption and decryption in secure communication protocols and data protection systems.
